Because of its strategic position and the possibility of its attack by roving Boer Commandos the British were forced to place the town under martial law for the duration of the war. However the presence of military forces also helped to increase the social life of the town with musical concerts, balls and performances by military bands
When peace was declared, the soldiers gradually departed and the Club Institution Buildings 
were purchased were purchased by Council for civic use.



